From 996524ab96a32e275b687e69eaeb5a24de3eed8e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ableton-wine <local@ableton-wine>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 22:46:10 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] shell32: reveal explorer /select targets through the XDG
 OpenURI portal

Live's Show in Explorer runs explorer.exe /select,"<path>" through
ShellExecute(Ex)W, and Wine satisfied it by spawning its own explorer
instead of the desktop's file manager (issue 41). SHELL_execute now
recognizes explorer /select command lines whose target exists and hands
the path to comdlg32's new __wine_portal_show_item export. That export
reuses the 0031 portal unix library to call
org.freedesktop.portal.OpenURI.OpenDirectory with a descriptor for the
target, which portal backends resolve to the containing folder with the
item selected (org.freedesktop.FileManager1 file managers). Only the
method reply is awaited, not the Response signal, so the caller's UI
thread does not sit behind the file manager launch.

The reveal is refused, and the old explorer spawn runs unchanged, when
FileDialogPortal is never, when the caller is 32-bit (no portal unix
library under new WoW64), when the target does not exist, or when the
portal call fails. comdlg32 imports shell32, so shell32 resolves the
export dynamically to avoid an import cycle.
---
